When registering, you can choose which parts of your body you’d be willing to donate – you can donate all,
or some of your organs and tissue. The more you’re willing to donate, the more people you can potentially help.
Anyone can register to donate their organs, and all of your personal information,
including any medical conditions, will be checked at the time of donation to ensure
that it’s safe to transplant your organs into other people.
